-- Tim Wins Third 4G, Rural Telephone Auction in Brazil
-- B y   C a r l a   S i m o e s
-- 2012-06-12T15:48:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-12/tim-wins-third-4g-rural-telephone-auction-in-brazil-correct-.html
(Corrects name of company in third paragraph.)  Tim Participacoes SA (TIMP3)  won the third
auction of licenses for 4G technology in Brazil and wireless
frequencies in the country’s rural areas, Brazil’s
telecommunications regulator, known as Anatel, said.  The company agreed to pay 340 million reais, or 7.9 percent
more than the minimum price of 315 million reais, according to
Anatel.  Tim will have obligations in the states of Parana,  Rio de
Janeiro , Santa Catarina and Espirito Santo for rural
frequencies, Anatel said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Carla Simoes in Brasilia Newsroom at 
 csimoes1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
